oads/2013/05/backupbuddy_sidebarad.png" width="280" height="250" /></a><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/go/backupbuddy">BackupBuddy</a> is a plugin that was created by the expert minds at <a href="http://ithemes.com/">iThemes</a> to help users easily backup, restore, and move their WordPress sites.</p>\n<p>Backup your themes, plugins, widgets, even your SQL database and files. It&#8217;s smart to backup your website on a regular basis and Backup Buddy makes that simple to do. You can send your backups wherever you feel is best, including DropBox, an email address, or an FTP.</p>\n<p>With BackupBuddy you&#8217;re able to restore everything that you&#8217;ve backed up in a very simple way. BackupBuddy alleviates the worry of what to do in the event that your WordPress site gets hacked or breaks due to an update or human error. All you have to do is upload &#8220;importbuddy.php&#8221; and your backup file and your entire site is in there, just how you left it!</p>\n<p>Moving your site to a different server/domain can also be a pain, but not with BackupBuddy. Being able to easily move sites from one domain to the other, is one of the main reason we recommend this plugin. It makes it simple for us to build a client site on our own dev server and then move it to their live domain.</p>\n<p>WebDevStudios loves BackupBuddy because of the hands-off reassurance it provides to our clients. BackupBuddy is an all in one backup solution that gives both us and our clients the peace of mind to know that their site has been backed up. The plugin also sends an email when a backup is taken so you . BackupBuddy gives you 24/7 assurance that your WordPress website is safe.</p>\n<p>Even if you are a WordPress novice BackupBuddy is something you want installed on your WordPress website. You may not have a clue what to do with a backup, but you can bring that backup to any development company or freelancer and they can take care of restoring the backup for you.</p>\n<p>Check out <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/go/backupbuddy" target="_blank">iThemes BackupBuddy</a> today!</p>\n<hr />\n<small style="font-size: 10px">**DISCLAIMER: WebDevStudios is an affiliate member of iThemes/BackupBuddy.  The links in this post are affiliate links which means that if you make a purchase after clicking the links in our post, we get a small payment from BackupBuddy as a thanks for promoting their product and brand.  WebDevStudios does not participate in affiliate programs of products that we do not love to use ourselves &#8211; - we fully endorse and regularly use the products we promote on our site.  If you have questions, let us know!</small></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/21/products-we-love-backupbuddy-from-ithemes/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:48:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"WordPress 10th Anniversary May 27th!";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/13/wordpress-10th-anniversary-may-27th-2/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:83:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/13/wordpress-10th-anniversary-may-27th-2/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 13 May 2013 16:08:05 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"Team";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"WordPress Meetup";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=7405";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:385:"Can you believe it has already been 10 years since the first release of WordPress? Back in 2003, no one knew that WordPress would take off like it has. Now yielding millions of users world wide, it has easily become &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/13/wordpress-10th-anniversary-may-27th-2/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2575:"<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/wordpress-10th-anniversay.png"><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-7408" alt="wordpress-10th-anniversay" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/wordpress-10th-anniversay-300x186.png" width="300" height="186" /></a>Can you believe it has already been 10 years since the first release of WordPress? Back in 2003, no one knew that WordPress would take off like it has. Now yielding millions of users world wide, it has easily become the biggest CMS platform out there.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Here at WebDevStudios we are more than joyful that WordPress has evolved the way it did because, well.. WordPress is what we do! All of our owners at WDS have been using WordPress for quite some time. <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-messenlehner/">Brian Messenlehner</a> and <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams </a>have been using the platform since early 2006, whereas, <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/">Lisa Sabin-Wilson</a> has been using WordPress since it&#8217;s release in 2003.</p>\n<p>In celebration of the <strong>10th anniversary</strong>, <a href="http://wordpress.org/">WordPress.org</a> has decided to have a little fun. They would like all of us &#8211; users, developers, designers.. everyone &#8211; to throw a party! Using <a href="http://www.meetup.com/everywhere/">Meetup Everywhere</a>, we can plan a party and invite people from all over. The process for setting up these parties is easy -</p>\n<blockquote>\n<ol>\n<li>Pick a place to go where a bunch of people can be merry  a park, a bar, a backyard, whatever</li>\n<li>Spread the word to local meetups, tech groups, press, etc and get people to say theyll come to your party</li>\n<li>If 50 or more people RSVP to your party, well try to send you some WordPress stickers and buttons</li>\n<li>Have party attendees post photos, videos, and the like with the #wp10 hashtag</li>\n</ol>\n</blockquote>\n<p>You can register your city and party on the <a href="http://www.meetup.com/WordPress/">official Meetup Everywhere 10th anniversary </a>site. You can also view full details on the party-a-thon on the <a href="http://wordpress.org/news/2013/04/save-the-date-may-27/">WordPress.org blog</a>.</p>\n<p>If you want to attend the Philly WP 10th anniversary party, sign up here! &#8211; <a href="http://www.meetup.com/Philadelphia-WordPress-Meetup-Group/events/118581782/">http://www.meetup.com/Philadelphia-WordPress-Meetup-Group/events/118581782/</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/13/wordpress-10th-anniversary-may-27th-2/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:4:"href";s:41:"http://feeds.feedburner.com/webdevstudios";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:3:"rel";s:3:"hub";s:4:"href";s:32:"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:3:{s:4:"info";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:3:"uri";s:13:"webdevstudios";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:14:"emailServiceId";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4