(181, 112, 'Bio', '<p>Aric Bostick is one of Americas top youth and education speakers and has shared his powerful message with over half a million students, educators and parents in the past decade.  As a former school teacher, and coach he has created a winning formula that teaches young people how to succeed in school and in life.  Aric also inspires educators and parents that are working to make a difference with Generation Y with strategies for connecting with youth of all ages and backgrounds. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Arics personal story of overcoming a family life that included divorce, alcoholism, emotional neglect and abuse and become the first in his family to graduate from college has given him the keen ability to inspire teens from all walks of life and make him one of the most sought after school assembly speakers as well as conference keynotes in the country.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>He has worked with hundreds of school districts nationwide and keynoted for some of the largest leadership organizations in America.  He has spoken for the National GEAR UP Conference, National BPA Conference, Regional FCCLA conferences, State FFA conferences, People to People Ambassador programs, and countless State Student Council, Dropout Prevention and Tobacco prevention conferences. </p> \r\n\r\n<p>He also shares his expertise from his classroom days and fifteen years of experience in working with todays youth with thousands of educators and parents each year by leading staff development days, parent nights and doing opening school district convocations to kick the year off with energy and enthusiasm!\r\n</p>\r\n<p>Aric Bostick is quite literally a one-stop shop for your school district or conference!  He can motivate students, educators and parents to be their best and connect with others to create an environment of success and leadership. </p>'),
