(415, 1, '2013-06-27 08:16:03', '2013-06-27 08:16:03', '<p>Mike is a professional speaker that puts his actions before his words. Rather than talking about what he has done or been through, Mike talks about what he''s doing.</p>\n <p>He specializes in speaking to students and professionals about topics like bullying, substance abuse, leadership and pursuing passions. Having worked with youth for more than a decade, Mike has founded and continues to direct two nationally-recognized non-profit organizations (the BAY and Skate for Change). Red Bull, TEDX (TED conferences), State Farm and people like Ryan Sheckler have taken notice of his reckless pursuit to help the disadvantaged. Maybe it''s time you take a look, too. </p>\n\n<p>He''s passionate. He''s real. He loves people. But most of all, he motivates others to live better lives. </p>\n\n', 'Mike Smith', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '127-autosave', '', '', '2013-06-27 08:16:03', '2013-06-27 08:16:03', '', 127, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers-dev/127-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(416, 1, '2013-06-25 06:20:04', '2013-06-25 06:20:04', 'Mike Smith  Youth motivational speaker  speaks to North Thurston students about making a better life for others. Mike Smith is a professional inspirational speaker based out of Lincoln Nebraska, He specializes in speaking to students and professionals about topics like bullying, substance abuse, leadership and pursuing passions. He is the founder of the Bay, a non profit skate park in Nebraska and a Skate for Change foundation. He has been featured by Red Bull, TEDX(TED conferences) and State Farm. North Thurston students found his presentation- highly inspirational, motivating and engaging. Here are some reviews from students at NTHS\r\n\r\nBrooklyn Falter  thought he connected well with students in high school and how students can change the climate in your school by making a difference for one person at a time. She liked what Mike said about getting out of your comfort zone and thinking about the legacy you want to leave behind at your school.\r\n\r\nSamantha Minor  thought Mike was very inspiring and that the story of his high school experience really connected and resonated with student here at NTHS.\r\n', 'Mike Smith', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '127-revision-25', '', '', '2013-06-25 06:20:04', '2013-06-25 06:20:04', '', 127, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers-dev/127-revision-25/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
