evStudios";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://webdevstudios.com/?p=7467";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:420:"Brad Williams is speaking at the upcoming event, WordCamp Orange County! This event will be held on June 1st through the 2nd at Vanguard University. Brad is speaking twice, and is doing a very exciting DradCast with Dre Armeda. The &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/23/brad-williams-is-speaking-at-wordcamp-orange-county-2013/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Melissa Hoppe";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3260:"<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams</a> is speaking at the upcoming event, <a href="http://2013.oc.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Orange County</a>! This event will be held on June 1st through the 2nd at Vanguard University. Brad is speaking twice, and is doing a very exciting <a href="http://dradcast.com/">DradCast</a> with <a href="https://twitter.com/armeda">Dre Armeda</a>.</p>\n<p><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/WCOC.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-7469" alt="WCOC" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/WCOC.png" width="840" height="196" /></a></p>\n<p>The first talk takes place on Saturday the 1st, in Track 2, at 9:00 AM. He will be speaking about how to keep your WordPress website secure.</p>\n<p><strong>Description</strong>:</p>\n<blockquote><p>Learn how to keep your WordPress-powered website secure from hackers and exploits. Brad Williams from <a href="http://webdevstudios.com/">WebDevStudios.com</a> shows examples of hacked sites, shares tips and plugins for keeping WordPress secure, and talks about his experiences with WordPress and security.</p></blockquote>\n<p><strong><a href="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/dradcast_logo_clean-e1361984643127.png"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-7253 alignright" alt="dradcast_logo_clean" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/dradcast_logo_clean-e1361984643127-150x150.png" width="150" height="150" /></a>Also on Saturday at 2:50 PM, in Track 1, Brad and Dre will be doing their very first LIVE <a href="http://dradcast.com/">DradCast</a> on a stage!</strong><strong> </strong></p>\n<p>For those of you who don&#8217;t know what <a href="http://dradcast.com/">DradCast</a> is:</p>\n<blockquote><p>The DradCast is a weekly podcast covering all things WordPress. Hosted by <a href="https://twitter.com/dremeda">Dre Armeda</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/williamsba">Brad Williams</a> (DRAD), and a special guest host each week.</p></blockquote>\n<p>At 7:00 PM on Saturday, the after party is being held at <a href="http://www.durtynellysoc.com/">Durty Nellys</a>. If you didn&#8217;t get the chance to meet up and chat with Brad during the sessions, you can catch him in the less professional atmosphere while at the after party!</p>\n<p>The second talk he&#8217;s presenting will be held on Sunday the 2nd, in the Plugin Workshop, at 2:00 PM. He will be speaking on the plugin Custom Post Type UI, which was written by the WordPress wiz himself!</p>\n<p><strong>Description</strong>:</p>\n<div>\n<blockquote><p><a href="http://wordpress.org/plugins/custom-post-type-ui/">Custom Post Type UI </a>is anAdmin UI for creating custom post types and custom taxonomies in WordPress.</p>\n<p>This plugin provides an easy to use interface to create and administer custom post types and taxonomies in WordPress. This plugin is created for WordPress 3.x.</p></blockquote>\n<p>If you&#8217;re attending <a href="http://2013.oc.wordcamp.org/">WordCamp Orange County</a> this year, make sure you check out all the awesome things that Brad is up to at this event. He is, as always, looking forward to meeting new people and reconnecting with those he&#8217;s already met!</p>\n</div>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:98:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/23/brad-williams-is-speaking-at-wordcamp-orange-county-2013/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:51:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"Products We Love: BackupBuddy from iThemes";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:78:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/21/products-we-love-backupbuddy-from-ithemes/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"http://webdevstudios.com/2013/05/21/products-we-love-backupbuddy-from-ithemes/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";