(123, 1, '2013-06-06 06:35:53', '2013-06-06 06:35:53', '<p class="orange font-15px">Success In Under 4 Minutes</p>\r\nOne little known fact about Eddie Slowikowski is that he is a Sub-4 miler.  He ran the mile in 3 minutes 59.6 seconds.  Hes one of only 275 American runners to attain this level of excellence.  Eddie uses the components of elite training for people to apply to achieve success in any facet of their lives.\r\n\r\n<p class="orange font-15px">The Power of One  </p>\r\nDo you realize how powerful you are? Within every one of us is the ability to take charge of our lives and develop concrete action plans for the future. The positive actions of one person can have a ripple effect on a community of people. Eddie guides students on that path to empowerment through self-esteem exercises and real solutions for today''s youth.\r\n\r\n<p class="orange font-15px">Flying High With Your Dreams  </p>\r\nThe first step to dream achievement is focus. Look past the negative influences and focus on the possibilities life has to offer. Participants learn energizing techniques, the importance of mentors and the skills that allow you to fly high with your dreams, not drugs!\r\n\r\n<p class="orange font-15px">True Values  </p>\r\nWhat is truly valuable in life? What do you believe in? In this powerful presentation, young people confront bigger issues in life. They learn through a thought provoking exercises that a person''s values system provides a framework for empowerment. Build a foundation of principle that will guide you on a proactive life.\r\n\r\n<p class="orange font-15px">Setting the Pace  </p>\r\nDo you have what it takes to be a leader for your peers? Eddie takes students on a journey of what it is to lead and what it is to follow. In every situation, we have a choice to take the lead for ourselves and set the pace for others or get in line and follow. It''s up to you to decide and Eddie takes participants through a series of exercises that gives them the tools to make powerful decisions that can change the shape of their lives.\r\n\r\n<p class="orange font-15px">Success is 90% Attitude</p>\r\nA program for a teacher in-service. Educators often put everyone else first in their lives. Reverse the process - if you can''t be good to yourself, you can''t be good to your students. Let off some steam and have some fun.\r\n \r\nOther topics that can be customized:\r\n Warning SignsHow to handle suicide prevention.\r\n\r\nFreshman FocusMentoring program with high school students learning how to assume a leadership role with incoming students from the local junior high schools. Serves as a guide to ease the transition from middle school to high school.\r\n \r\n<p class="orange font-15px">Take the Shot</p>\r\nThrough his years of accomplishment in the world of sports, Eddie learned the importance of teamwork. Without being selfless for the team, we can''t truly be successful on our own terms. With exercises designed to build team rapport and teach us about our behavioral styles, Eddie creates an "all for one" mentality that lights the way to individual success.\r\n \r\nBilly''s StoryA tragic story of the impact of drunk driving on innocent lives.\r\n \r\nPick on Someone Your Own Size!How to take the bite out of bullying.\r\n \r\nCrossroadsHow the decisions we make affect ourselves, the people around us and the people we''ve yet to meet.\r\n \r\nReady, Set, GO!Orientation special on how to enter the brave new world with tools that help you thrive.\r\n', 'Eddie Slowikowski', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'eddie-slowikowski', '', '', '2013-07-16 08:45:01', '2013-07-16 08:45:01', '', 0, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/?post_type=speakers&#038;p=123', 0, 'speakers', '', 0),
