(184, 1, '2013-06-08 09:16:24', '2013-06-08 09:16:24', 'Patrick "Pac Man" Perez\r\nMAD SKILLS FOR STUDENT SUCCESS\r\n \r\nWith shows like America''s Best Dance Crew and Dancing With the Stars tearing up the airwaves you might think you''ve seen it all until now! Get your students ready for some caffeine for their dreams and some sugar for their souls because their lives are about to get a lot sweeter! \r\n\r\nStudent success author and super-fresh Latino youth speaker Patrick Pac Man Perez combines the eye-catching style of break dance (b-boying) with pop music, student interaction and student success principles that deal directly with:\r\n+ Drug |Alcohol| Tobacco Prevention \r\n+Choices \r\n+Leadership/Goal Setting\r\n+Drop Out Prevention/Higher Education\r\n+ Gang Prevention*\r\n +Pregnancy/STD Prevention**\r\n\r\nIdeal for: Leadership Conferences| School Motivational Assemblies| Migrant Programs\r\n\r\nNo other student success program offers the style and flavor that Patrick brings! Patrick has performed to over 300,000 people across the USA, Canada, Mexico and Germany. Patrick''s passion is to use his gifts in order to reach out to those students who are in need of hope, encouragement or just a good kick in the pants to get going!\r\n\r\n', 'Patrick Perez', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '116-revision-4', '', '', '2013-06-08 09:16:24', '2013-06-08 09:16:24', '', 116, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/116-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(186, 1, '2013-06-11 11:20:36', '2013-06-11 11:20:36', 'Conference Keynote/Assembly Presentation:\r\nBe a Catalyst\r\nScotts presentations begin as a giant party. In one moment, students are laughing hysterically, moving actively on their feet, and shouting ROCK ON! at the top of their lungs. Yet only minutes later, that same room is silent; students find themselves hanging on to every word of Scotts heartfelt and challenging message. It is at this point that the students in attendance realize they are no longer watching a presentation to an audience of hundreds or even thousandsthey are hearing their own personal call to action.\r\n\r\nScott is different because he doesnt demand anything. He simply asks students what they should be demanding from themselves and from each other getting them to aspire to a higher calling, a higher purpose.  Scotts speech laid the groundwork for our entire leadership program.\r\n- Craig Sutphin, Director of Student Leadership, St. Marys HS, Berkeley, CA\r\n\r\nScott gets that students have a HUGE impact on those around themfrom their casual acquaintances at school to the close friends they see virtually 24/7. Each and every student has the power to influence their world in some way, shape, or form. Before changing anything, though, each student must undoubtedly recognize that the world in which they live is not perfect by any means. It takes passion and determination to make it a better place.\r\nRegardless of the situation, capacity, or context, the only way students will truly change their circumstances is if they decide to be a catalystsomeone who changes the status quo.\r\n\r\nPast Speech Topics / Workshops Include\r\nRespect\r\nSchool Spirit\r\nIssue Awareness\r\nStandardized Testing\r\nFreshman Orientation\r\nSenior Institute Days\r\nBullying\r\nPublic Speaking\r\nStudent Activity Planning\r\nand many more\r\n\r\n', 'Scott Backovich', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '119-revision-8', '', '', '2013-06-11 11:20:36', '2013-06-11 11:20:36', '', 119, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/119-revision-8/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(188, 1, '2013-06-14 09:45:46', '2013-06-14 09:45:46', '<b>Taking the Stairs </b>\r\n(youth and adults)\r\nTiana Tozer "wheels" on stage and immediately puts her audience at ease by addressing the humorous issues of her disability. She explains that although many funny things have happened to her since she has been in a wheelchair, there is nothing humorous about how she lost her freedom to stand tall and walk. Tiana continues to capture the audience as she shares her recovery journey -- the victories and the setbacks. Skillfully, she then challenges the student''s complacency towards the legal drug of alcohol.\r\nAfter sharing her hospital stories, Tiana illustrates the power of choices through role playing with audience volunteers. She speaks about the unimportance of physical looks, emphasizing the importance of actions and behavior. Tiana will affirm everyone''s power to make choices and then challenges them to accept responsibility for their choices -- past and those to come.\r\nTiana offers unique insight into what happens after the party. She has spoken at hundreds of high schools for MADD, she has presented at student leadership conferences, judicial conferences, pre-prom and Red Ribbon Week programs, and she lobbied for the .08 law in Idaho, Illinois and Nevada.\r\nIn "Taking the Stairs" Tiana can focus on:\r\n	Drinking and Driving \r\n	Drug Use \r\n	Peer Pressure \r\n	Self-Image \r\n	Athletes and Alcohol \r\n	Responsible Choices \r\n	General Motivation \r\n       Student Leadership\r\n', 'Tiana Tozer ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '155-revision-3', '', '', '2013-06-14 09:45:46', '2013-06-14 09:45:46', '', 155, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/155-revision-3/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(189, 1, '2013-06-17 11:30:15', '2013-06-17 11:30:15', '<b>Students:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>HEROES ROCK!</br>\r\nROCK YOUR LIFE AND OTHERS WILL FOLLOW</b>\r\n\r\nR  Get Real about who you are, who your not and who really want to be!\r\nO  Be Optimistic that your goals and dreams are possible no matter what challenges you currently face!\r\nC  Build Confidence by taking action everyday toward your goals and making the right choices that support your lifes dreams! \r\nK  Be Kind to everyone on your path to success, they will follow your lead!\r\nStudents Will Learn How to:\r\n	Overcome their past and create hope for their future!\r\n	Create a vision for what they want in life and take action to make it a reality!\r\n	Be a real HERO by spreading kindness to all those they meet and lead by example! \r\n\r\nEducator Training:\r\n\r\n<b><i>From Burnout to Breakthrough\r\n Simple Strategies the Everyday Hero can take to keep their fire alive!</b></i>\r\n\r\nBeing an educator, counselor or youth advocate is one of the most rewarding occupations in the world.  However, it is also one of the most challenging, underappreciated, and exhausting jobs one can possibly take on.  If you have ever lost your focus, lost your passion or simply felt burnout by the enormous task of being all things to all people then this workshop will be just what the doctor ordered.  Get ready to be rejuvenated, refocused and fired up to make a difference once again!\r\nAttendees receive a Burnout to Breakthrough guide and Will Learn How to:\r\n	Remember your purpose and rise above the bureaucracy and trivial\r\n	Build lasting relationships with your students that keep you energized\r\n	Happiness and Health Tips that will keep your tank full so you have more to give!\r\n\r\nParents Training:  \r\n\r\n<b><i>How to be an AWESOME Parent!\r\n7 Steps to Being the Parent You were Meant to Be!</b></i>\r\n\r\n<p>Being a Parent is the toughest job on the planet.  It is the only job in life that you will never lose, never quit or ever get fired from. There are no qualifications to be a parent and few parents are ever taught how to do the job of parenting well.  Until now!  There are 7 simple steps every parent can take each day to be an AWESOME Parent! This is a cant miss message for any parent wanting to change their life and inspire their children to follow their lead! </p>\r\n\r\nParents Will Learn How to:\r\n	Create a loving relationship with their children \r\n	Accept their children as they are and encourage them each day\r\n	Model success and self  esteem by walking your talk and pursuing your own goals and dreams\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Aric Bostick', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '112-revision-7', '', '', '2013-06-17 11:30:15', '2013-06-17 11:30:15', '', 112, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/112-revision-7/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(191, 1, '2013-06-17 11:33:20', '2013-06-17 11:33:20', 'Mike Smith  Youth motivational speaker  speaks to North Thurston students about making a better life for others. Mike Smith is a professional inspirational speaker based out of Lincoln Nebraska, He specializes in speaking to students and professionals about topics like bullying, substance abuse, leadership and pursuing passions. He is the founder of the Bay, a non profit skate park in Nebraska and a Skate for Change foundation. He has been featured by Red Bull, TEDX(TED conferences) and State Farm. North Thurston students found his presentation- highly inspirational, motivating and engaging. Here are some reviews from students at NTHS\r\n\r\nBrooklyn Falter  thought he connected well with students in high school and how students can change the climate in your school by making a difference for one person at a time. She liked what Mike said about getting out of your comfort zone and thinking about the legacy you want to leave behind at your school.\r\n\r\nSamantha Minor  thought Mike was very inspiring and that the story of his high school experience really connected and resonated with student here at NTHS.\r\n', 'Mike Smith', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '127-revision-10', '', '', '2013-06-17 11:33:20', '2013-06-17 11:33:20', '', 127, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/127-revision-10/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(192, 1, '2013-06-17 11:31:33', '2013-06-17 11:31:33', 'Success In Under 4 Minutes\r\nOne little known fact about Eddie Slowikowski is that he is a Sub-4 miler.  He ran the mile in 3 minutes 59.6 seconds.  Hes one of only 275 American runners to attain this level of excellence.  Eddie uses the components of elite training for people to apply to achieve success in any facet of their lives.\r\n\r\nThe Power of One  \r\nDo you realize how powerful you are? Within every one of us is the ability to take charge of our lives and develop concrete action plans for the future. The positive actions of one person can have a ripple effect on a community of people. Eddie guides students on that path to empowerment through self-esteem exercises and real solutions for today''s youth.\r\n\r\nFlying High With Your Dreams  \r\nThe first step to dream achievement is focus. Look past the negative influences and focus on the possibilities life has to offer. Participants learn energizing techniques, the importance of mentors and the skills that allow you to fly high with your dreams, not drugs!\r\n\r\nTrue Values  \r\nWhat is truly valuable in life? What do you believe in? In this powerful presentation, young people confront bigger issues in life. They learn through a thought provoking exercises that a person''s values system provides a framework for empowerment. Build a foundation of principle that will guide you on a proactive life.\r\n\r\nSetting the Pace  \r\nDo you have what it takes to be a leader for your peers? Eddie takes students on a journey of what it is to lead and what it is to follow. In every situation, we have a choice to take the lead for ourselves and set the pace for others or get in line and follow. It''s up to you to decide and Eddie takes participants through a series of exercises that gives them the tools to make powerful decisions that can change the shape of their lives.\r\n\r\nSuccess is 90% Attitude\r\nA program for a teacher in-service. Educators often put everyone else first in their lives. Reverse the process - if you can''t be good to yourself, you can''t be good to your students. Let off some steam and have some fun.\r\n \r\nOther topics that can be customized:\r\n Warning SignsHow to handle suicide prevention.\r\n\r\nFreshman FocusMentoring program with high school students learning how to assume a leadership role with incoming students from the local junior high schools. Serves as a guide to ease the transition from middle school to high school.\r\n \r\nTake the Shot\r\nThrough his years of accomplishment in the world of sports, Eddie learned the importance of teamwork. Without being selfless for the team, we can''t truly be successful on our own terms. With exercises designed to build team rapport and teach us about our behavioral styles, Eddie creates an "all for one" mentality that lights the way to individual success.\r\n \r\nBilly''s StoryA tragic story of the impact of drunk driving on innocent lives.\r\n \r\nPick on Someone Your Own Size!How to take the bite out of bullying.\r\n \r\nCrossroadsHow the decisions we make affect ourselves, the people around us and the people we''ve yet to meet.\r\n \r\nReady, Set, GO!Orientation special on how to enter the brave new world with tools that help you thrive.\r\n', 'Eddie Slowikowski', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '123-revision-6', '', '', '2013-06-17 11:31:33', '2013-06-17 11:31:33', '', 123, 'http://biziindia.com/finaospeakers/123-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
